&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Marksman Security is built on serving our clients and building careers – just like yours. We are trusted by some of the most well-known companies and properties in the country while remaining dedicated to building personalized security solutions that solve the needs of every customer we support. Named as a nationally recognized Top Workplace in 2024 and 2025 by USA Today, Marksman&#39;s customized approach to security services will provide you with the opportunity to learn, grow and succeed. Our core values of being Unified, Transparent, Innovative, Committed and Accountable help us in providing unparalleled service and support in all that we do. If you are looking for a meaningful career, a culture of excellence, and the ability to make a difference, we want to talk to you!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;unarmed 1st shift security officers&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary:&lt;/strong&gt; We are seeking vigilant and responsible Unarmed 1st Shift Security Officers to join our team. The role involves ensuring the safety and security of our premises during designated hours. The ideal candidate will possess strong observational skills and a commitment to maintaining a safe environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and patrol assigned areas to detect and prevent security breaches.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respond promptly to alarms and investigate disturbances.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Report any suspicious activities, hazards, or unusual occurrences immediately.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a daily log of activities and incidents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide excellent customer service to all visitors and staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in enforcing company policies and procedures to ensure a secure environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High school diploma or equivalent.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience in a security-related field is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication and interpersonal skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to remain calm and composed in high-pressure situations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic proficiency in using security equipment and technology.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently and as part of a team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must pass a background check and have a valid security guard license.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Marksman Security is built on serving our clients and building careers – just like yours. We are trusted by some of the most well-known companies and properties in the country while remaining dedicated to building personalized security solutions that solve the needs of every customer we support. Named as a nationally recognized Top Workplace in 2024 and 2025 by USA Today, Marksman&#39;s customized approach to security services will provide you with the opportunity to learn, grow and succeed. Our core values of being Unified, Transparent, Innovative, Committed and Accountable help us in providing unparalleled service and support in all that we do. If you are looking for a meaningful career, a culture of excellence, and the ability to make a difference, we want to talk to you!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;unarmed 2nd shift security officer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary:&lt;/strong&gt; We are seeking a dedicated and vigilant Unarmed 2nd Shift Security Officer to maintain a safe and secure environment for our premises. This role requires keen attention to detail and a proactive approach to identifying potential security risks during the second shift hours.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and authorize entrance and departure of employees, visitors, and other persons to maintain security of premises.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Patrol industrial or commercial premises to prevent and detect signs of intrusion and ensure security of doors, windows, and gates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write reports of daily activities and irregularities, such as equipment or property damage, theft, presence of unauthorized persons, or unusual occurrences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Answer alarms and investigate disturbances.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain order and protect property during the second shift.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respond to emergencies and provide necessary assistance as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate effectively with other security personnel and report any suspicious activities promptly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High school diploma or equivalent.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience as a security officer or relevant position.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong observational skills and attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently and remain calm in emergency situations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic computer knowledge to complete reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexibility to work 2nd shift hours, including weekends and holidays.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Marksman Security is built on serving our clients and building careers – just like yours. We are trusted by some of the most well-known companies and properties in the country while remaining dedicated to building personalized security solutions that solve the needs of every customer we support. Named as a nationally recognized Top Workplace in 2024 and 2025 by USA Today, Marksman&#39;s customized approach to security services will provide you with the opportunity to learn, grow and succeed. Our core values of being Unified, Transparent, Innovative, Committed and Accountable help us in providing unparalleled service and support in all that we do. If you are looking for a meaningful career, a culture of excellence, and the ability to make a difference, we want to talk to you!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;unarmed 3rd shift unarmed security officer&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary:&lt;/strong&gt; Join our team as an Unarmed 3rd Shift Security Officer, ensuring the safety and security of our premises during nighttime hours. This role is crucial for maintaining a secure environment for employees and visitors, preventing unauthorized access, and promptly responding to incidents.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and patrol assigned areas to ensure the safety and security of the premises&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform regular inspections of doors, windows, and gates to ensure they are secure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Report any suspicious activities, security breaches, or hazards to the appropriate authorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respond promptly to alarms or incidents, and provide assistance as necessary&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain clear and concise logs of daily activities, incidents, and observations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with crowd control and ensure orderly conduct during events or emergencies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide excellent customer service to employees and visitors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High school diploma or equivalent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience in security or a related field is preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong observational and problem-solving skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and interpersonal skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to remain calm and handle stressful situations effectively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be able to work night shifts, weekends, and holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Valid driver&#39;s license and reliable transportation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to pass a background check&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Marksman Security is built on serving our clients and building careers – just like yours. We are trusted by some of the most well-known companies and properties in the country while remaining dedicated to building personalized security solutions that solve the needs of every customer we support. Named as a nationally recognized Top Workplace in 2024 and 2025 by USA Today, Marksman&#39;s customized approach to security services will provide you with the opportunity to learn, grow and succeed. Our core values of being Unified, Transparent, Innovative, Committed and Accountable help us in providing unparalleled service and support in all that we do. If you are looking for a meaningful career, a culture of excellence, and the ability to make a difference, we want to talk to you!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities &lt;/strong&gt;include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Maintain Visibility:&lt;/strong&gt; Ensure high visibility by periodically stopping and patrolling different areas of the lot to deter criminal activity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Access Control / Verify Credentials: &lt;/strong&gt;Ensure that individuals attempting to enter the facility have proper identification and access passes, such as badges, cards, or visitor passes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Surveillance&lt;/strong&gt;: Continuously monitor CCTV cameras placed around the gate area to identify suspicious activities, unauthorized entry, or any security breaches.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Monitor Entry and Exit Points:&lt;/strong&gt; Ensure that only authorized personnel and vehicles are entering or exiting the lot by checking identification, vehicle registration, or other access control protocols.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Log Entries and Exits of Trucks&lt;/strong&gt;: Keep a detailed log of all trucks entering or leaving the premises, including company name, driver name, truck ID number, cargo type, and delivery or pick-up details.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Observe for Security Threats:&lt;/strong&gt; Watch for suspicious behavior, loitering individuals, or any signs of illegal activities such as theft, vandalism, or drug use.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Incident Reporting:&lt;/strong&gt; Immediately report any security breaches, safety hazards, or emergencies to the appropriate authorities or management, and document the incident thoroughly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ARMED PILB / Guard Card&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be at least 21 years of age&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have a valid driver&#39;s license&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High School diploma or general education degree (GED)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to pass pre-employment drug screen and criminal background check&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience in security is preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay and Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid time off and paid holidays!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunities for career growth and promotion!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Medical, dental, and vision benefits!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pension/Retirement 401K benefits!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skills-enhancing training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;EOE/M/F/D/V&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;#IND4&lt;/p&gt;

