&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Marksman Security is built on serving our clients and building careers – just like yours. We are trusted by some of the most well-known companies and properties in the country while remaining dedicated to building personalized security solutions that solve the needs of every customer we support. Named as a nationally recognized Top Workplace in 2024 and 2025 by USA Today, Marksman&#39;s customized approach to security services will provide you with the opportunity to learn, grow and succeed. Our core values of being Unified, Transparent, Innovative, Committed and Accountable help us in providing unparalleled service and support in all that we do. If you are looking for a meaningful career, a culture of excellence, and the ability to make a difference, we want to talk to you!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Titan Security is looking for professional, people-oriented &lt;strong&gt;Armed&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong data-start=&quot;555&quot; data-end=&quot;582&quot;&gt;Security Patrol Officers&lt;/strong&gt; to join our Public Safety Team. As a key part of our safety operations, you’ll help ensure a secure, welcoming environment for our guests, tenants, and staff across our retail, dining, and entertainment areas in the Myrtle Beach Area. If you’re dependable, calm under pressure, and enjoy engaging with the public, this is the role for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Responsibilities include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform regular foot and vehicle patrols throughout the property, including retail stores, restaurants, parking lots, entertainment zones, and pedestrian walkways.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide courteous assistance to guests, offering directions, answering questions, and creating a visible, approachable presence to enhance the overall visitor experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respond promptly and professionally to disturbances, emergencies, medical situations, or suspicious activity. Initiate appropriate action and coordinate with local authorities or emergency services as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the surveillance team to monitor CCTV systems and report irregular activities or safety concerns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain detailed incident and activity reports, including logs of patrol rounds, observed hazards, and guest interactions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with managing pedestrian and vehicle traffic during peak hours, events, or special promotions, ensuring smooth flow and safety for guests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with retail tenants to identify and deter theft or fraud, and support store managers with internal investigations if necessary.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct routine checks of doors, windows, lighting, and fire safety equipment to ensure all facilities are secure and operational.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promote awareness of property rules, safety protocols, and emergency procedures to guests and staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize communication and conflict resolution skills to peacefully manage difficult situations or disputes between guests, vendors, or staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other duties as assigned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High school diploma or equivalent required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be at least 21 years of age&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have SLED security license&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 6 months of experience in security, law enforcement, or a customer-facing role preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Valid driver’s license and clean driving record&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to obtain and maintain any state or local security license or certification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication and conflict-resolution skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be able to stand, walk, or patrol for extended periods and work outdoors in various weather conditions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be available for weekends, and holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to pass

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Marksman Security is built on serving our clients and building careers – just like yours. We are trusted by some of the most well-known companies and properties in the country while remaining dedicated to building personalized security solutions that solve the needs of every customer we support. Named as a nationally recognized Top Workplace in 2024 and 2025 by USA Today, Marksman&#39;s customized approach to security services will provide you with the opportunity to learn, grow and succeed. Our core values of being Unified, Transparent, Innovative, Committed and Accountable help us in providing unparalleled service and support in all that we do. If you are looking for a meaningful career, a culture of excellence, and the ability to make a difference, we want to talk to you!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot; data-start=&quot;104&quot; data-end=&quot;152&quot;&gt;Assistant Director of Retail Security&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot; data-start=&quot;153&quot; data-end=&quot;222&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;153&quot; data-end=&quot;166&quot;&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Salt Lake City,UT&lt;br data-start=&quot;179&quot; data-end=&quot;182&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;182&quot; data-end=&quot;195&quot;&gt;Pay Rate: $52K-$54K&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot; data-start=&quot;278&quot; data-end=&quot;554&quot;&gt;At &lt;span class=&quot;hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;whitespace-normal&quot;&gt;Marksman Security Corporation&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, we live by our core values: &lt;strong data-start=&quot;348&quot; data-end=&quot;405&quot;&gt;Integrity | Service | Commitment | Drive | Innovation&lt;/strong&gt;. We are currently seeking a motivated and experienced &lt;strong data-start=&quot;460&quot; data-end=&quot;495&quot;&gt;Assistant Director of Retail Security Operations&lt;/strong&gt; to lead security services at a premier site in Utah.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot; data-start=&quot;556&quot; data-end=&quot;691&quot;&gt;If you are passionate about leadership, operational excellence, and delivering exceptional security services, we want to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr data-start=&quot;693&quot; data-end=&quot;696&quot;&gt;
&lt;h3 style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot; data-start=&quot;698&quot; data-end=&quot;720&quot;&gt;Position Summary&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot; data-start=&quot;721&quot; data-end=&quot;1106&quot;&gt;Assistant Director is responsible for overseeing all on-site security personnel and operations. This role ensures proper staffing, officer training, compliance with policies and procedures, and strong client relationships. You will work closely with the client and company leadership to achieve operational goals and maintain the highest standards of service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr data-start=&quot;1108&quot; data-end=&quot;1111&quot;&gt;
&lt;h3 data-start=&quot;1113&quot; data-end=&quot;1139&quot;&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul data-start=&quot;1141&quot; data-end=&quot;2099&quot;&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1141&quot; data-end=&quot;1223&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1143&quot; data-end=&quot;1223&quot;&gt;Provide professional interaction with clients, residents, guests, and visitors&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1224&quot; data-end=&quot;1304&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1226&quot; data-end=&quot;1304&quot;&gt;Build and maintain strong client relationships through ongoing communication&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1305&quot; data-end=&quot;1377&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1307&quot; data-end=&quot;1377&quot;&gt;Develop and implement site-specific security policies and procedures&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1378&quot; data-end=&quot;1502&quot;&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Marksman Security is built on serving our clients and building careers – just like yours. We are trusted by some of the most well-known companies and properties in the country while remaining dedicated to building personalized security solutions that solve the needs of every customer we support. Named as a nationally recognized Top Workplace in 2024 and 2025 by USA Today, Marksman&#39;s customized approach to security services will provide you with the opportunity to learn, grow and succeed. Our core values of being Unified, Transparent, Innovative, Committed and Accountable help us in providing unparalleled service and support in all that we do. If you are looking for a meaningful career, a culture of excellence, and the ability to make a difference, we want to talk to you!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Marksman Security&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Assistant Security Supervisors&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;All Shifts&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Weekend and holiday availability may be required&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;The ideal candidate will have previous experience in security, military or law enforcement. State training and licensing assistance may be available for qualified candidates.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help supervise operations of an assigned Client site on assigned shift.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Report directly to Site Supervisor/Director and/or Marksman&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage a team of security officers, including participating in scheduling, payroll, training, coaching, development and support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the Client Site is provided with high quality security services to protect people and property.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle all escalated security issues or emergency situations appropriately.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop staff in both technical and professional skills through performance management (coaching, recognition, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide the basis of a great work environment by treating staff with respect.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the&amp;nbsp; Coordination and/or conduct site-specific “on the job training”, client–specific training and annual refresher training for staff by adhering to Marksman training standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reconcile logs, shift responsibilities and patrols; review incident reports prior to submitting to Site Supervisor and/or Director and coordinate preliminary investigations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop/maintain operational procedures and post orders that are always available for emergency reference by staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Train and qualify to work assigned post. Understands the specific and general post instructions for that assigned post. Maintain practical knowledge of all additional and emergency post instructions that are called for by the client.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain access control procedures set by building management.&lt;/li&gt;
